      "writtenOn": "2018-09-18T18:26:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So this design is the same as the old way of doing things with webhooks:\nIf there are multiple requests for the same task (issue+patchset) then a new job is not triggered, it is just tacked onto the existing run (https://bugs.chromium.org/p/skia/issues/detail?id\u003d7608).\nThis is done because the number of checkouts on the Android compile server is limited and it is easy to overload so we want to optimize when possible.",
      "parentUuid": "94c22d15_b884d188",
      "range": {
